cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a generative model for natural textures, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses 2D and 3D textures, which are commonly used in computer graphics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep learning techniques to learn the texture space. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a generative model that can be used for texture interpolation and learning 3D textures from 2D exemplars, which are applications of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses MLPs (multi-layer perceptrons) to sample the texture space, which is a type of neural network.
